main event: An unidentified flying object was reported to the Baltimore Filter Center, Maryland, at 09/02332Z Sept 55. The object had first been seen by another observer at the same post at 09/0302Z. The UFOB was last seen by GCI observers at 09/0312Z Sept 55.
interesting points: The object seemed neither to gain nor lose altitude and had a variable form or definite body shape, although it seemed always to maintain a general circular or oval outline.
The object appeared to pulse and there was a constant variation in the intensity of the whitish light which was emitted. This light was very bright and seemed to pulsate or wink.
The lights observed hovered on successive occasions over the approximate area for a period of 45-60 minutes. At times the lights appeared to shoot out the sides of the undefined object.

There were some aircraft in the sky throughout the period of the sighting and at times seemed to be blinking lights, but in the observer's opinion, they were coming from aircraft considerably beyond the object.
No photographs were taken of the UFO.
sighted object: circular or oval-shaped object with pulsing, bright whitish lights
witnesses: 1/Lt Hurlbut E. Bonnie and Mr. Albert Merzel
